## Where this repo sits

One agent per vault, plus a shared ops repo:

```
{{LOCAL_ROOT}}/
  agents/
    {{AGENT_NAME}}/          <- YOU ARE HERE: librarian for {{VAULT_NAME}}
    <sibling-agent>/         <- same architecture, different vault
  {{VAULT_NAME}}/            <- the vault this librarian writes to
  <sibling-vault>/           <- never touched by this agent (except read-only via query-vault)
  {{OPS_REPO}}/              <- launchd plists, backup, wiki-ingest scripts
```

The agent writes to exactly one vault. Cross-vault access, where granted, is READ-ONLY through the `query-vault` skill.

---

## Why this librarian exists

1. **Capture has to be one-tap-fast.** Telegram is always open; Obsidian-on-phone is friction. Voice memos work because local Whisper transcribes them cleanly.
2. **LLMs silently drop file writes.** Letting an LLM decide whether and where to save a message failed in practice — ~5-15% of messages went missing or got mislabeled. The fix is a deterministic Python hook that writes before the LLM runs. The LLM's only job is to reply.
3. **Vault voice contamination.** One librarian per vault means zero cross-bleed between domains. Boundary is enforced at three layers (see below).

