## Under the hood

### The auto-save hook is the critical piece

Without this hook, saving becomes "ask the LLM nicely to write a file" — which fails at measurable rates. With the hook:

- The complete message body is read from the session JSONL (not the truncated ctx).
- `pathlib` + atomic `os.replace` means no partial writes.
- Drive URL detection and subprocess spawn happen in the same deterministic layer.
- If the LLM crashes mid-reply, the file is already saved.

Source: [`hooks/auto-save-inbox/handler.py`](./hooks/auto-save-inbox/handler.py). Trigger config: [`hooks/auto-save-inbox/HOOK.yaml`](./hooks/auto-save-inbox/HOOK.yaml).

### Model routing

`config.yaml` sets:

- `model.default: gpt-5.4-mini` via `provider: openai-codex` (covered by ChatGPT Pro).
- `smart_model_routing.cheap_model: gpt-5.4-nano` for trivial responses.
- `session_reset.telegram.idle_minutes: 60` — after an hour idle, next message starts a fresh session.
- `fallback_providers: [copilot]` — GitHub Copilot PAT auto-fallback.
- NO `anthropic` anywhere. Claude is reserved for the official `claude -p` CLI, called only from `{{OPS_REPO}}` scripts.

### Why `HERMES_HOME` IS the repo dir

Flat > nested. One repo per librarian, one HERMES_HOME per librarian, no path math. launchd plist is a one-liner: `WorkingDirectory = {{LOCAL_ROOT}}/agents/{{AGENT_NAME}}`, `EnvironmentVariables.HERMES_HOME = (same)`.

