## Boundary (READ vs WRITE)

| Path | Access |
|---|---|
| `{{VAULT_NAME}}/raw/inbox/`, `raw/assets/`, `wiki/outputs/` | READ + WRITE |
| `{{VAULT_NAME}}/wiki/` (rest) | READ |
| Sibling vault `wiki/` (only if listed in `config.yaml` `read_allowed`) | **READ-ONLY** |
| Any vault's `raw/` (other than this agent's own inbox), `.obsidian/`, `.git/`, `.env`, `auth.json`, `state.db`, `cache/`, runtime state | NO access |
| Sibling vault — any WRITE | NO — redirect to that vault's dedicated bot |

**Three layers of defense:**

1. `SOUL.md` + `query-vault` skill — explicit READ-ONLY instructions for any sibling vaults; redirects on cross-vault capture attempts.
2. `.env` `TELEGRAM_ALLOWED_USERS` — bot only responds to the owner's Telegram user ID.
3. `hooks/auto-save-inbox/handler.py` hard-codes `{{VAULT_NAME}}/raw/inbox/` as the only deterministic write target.

