## Backup and disaster recovery

This repo (librarian config, hooks, skills, SOUL, scripts) is committed and pushed on the schedule defined in `{{OPS_REPO}}/scripts/daily-backup.sh`. Runtime state (sessions, memories, state.db, gateway state, caches) is gitignored — per-machine, regenerated each session.

**What you LOSE on restore (acceptable):**
- Conversation history (`sessions/*.jsonl`).
- Long-term memories (`memories/`).
- Pairing state (sometimes) — re-pair via `hermes pairing approve`.

**What you KEEP (everything that matters):**
- SOUL.md, USER.md, MEMORY.md, config.yaml.
- All hooks (especially `auto-save-inbox`).
- All skills.
- Start script.

Full DR runbook: `{{LOCAL_ROOT}}/{{OPS_REPO}}/docs/RESTORE.md`.

